HIV/AIDS: Kasar Sin ta samu karin mutane 14 cikin 100
Kasar Sin ta samu karuwar yawan mutanen da ke dauke da cutar HIV da AIDS da kashi 14 cikin dari.
Jami'an kiwon lafiya sun ce an yi wa mutane fiye da 820,000 kamuwa a kasar.
Kimanin sabbin mutane 40,000 aka ruwaito a cikin kwata na biyu na 2018 kadai.
An samu ƙarin sababbin cututtuka ta hanyar jima'i, wanda ya bambanta da na baya.
A al'adance, cutar HIV tana yaduwa cikin sauri a wasu sassan kasar Sin sakamakon ƙarin jini da ke dauke da cutar.
Amma adadin mutanen da suka kamu da cutar HIV ta wannan hanyar ya ragu zuwa kusan babu, in ji hukumomin kiwon lafiya na kasar Sin a wani taro a lardin Yunnan.
Duk da haka, a kowace shekara, adadin mutanen da ke da cutar kanjamau da kanjamau a China yana ƙaruwa da mutane 100,000.
Yaduwar cutar kanjamau ta hanyar jima'i babbar matsala ce ga al'ummar LGBT a kasar Sin.
An haramta luwadi a kasar Sin a shekarar 1997, amma nuna bambanci ga mutanen LGBT yana da yawa.
Domin ɗabi'ar kasar, bincike ya nuna cewa kashi 70 zuwa 90 cikin ɗari na maza da ke kwana da maza za su auri mata.
Yawancin kamuwa da cutar ta hanyar rashin kariya ta jima'i a cikin waɗannan alaƙar.
Tun daga 2003, gwamnatin kasar Sin ta yi alkawarin samar da maganin cutar kanjamau ga kowa a kasar a matsayin wani bangare na kokarin magance cutar.
