Jakadan Amurka ya zargi China da cin zarafin 'yan jarida da talla
Mako guda bayan da wata jaridar kasar Sin ta wallafa wani talla mai shafi hudu a wata jaridar Amurka da ke nuna yadda cinikayya tsakanin Amurka da China ke amfanar juna, jakadan Amurka a China ya zargi Beijing da amfani da kafafen yada labaran Amurka don yada farfaganda.
Shugaban Amurka Donald Trump ya yi magana a ranar Laraba game da karin kudin da China Daily ta biya a jaridar Des Moines Register - jaridar da ta fi sayarwa a Iowa - bayan da ta zargi China da tsoma baki a zaben Amurka na ranar 6 ga watan Nuwamba, China ta yi watsi da zargin.
Zargin da Trump ya yi cewa Beijing na kokarin tsoma baki a zaben Amurka ya nuna wa kamfanin dillancin labarai na Reuters cewa, wannan sabon mataki ne a kokarin da Washington ke yi na matsa lamba kan kasar Sin.
Duk da yake al'ada ce ga gwamnatocin kasashen waje su fitar da tallace-tallace don inganta cinikayya, Beijing da Washington a halin yanzu suna cikin yakin cinikayya inda suke daidaita harajin shigo da kayayyaki da juna.
Kudaden da kasar Sin ta saka a farkon yakin cinikayya sun shafi masu fitar da kayayyaki daga jihohin tarayya kamar Iowa, wadanda ke goyon bayan jam'iyyar Republican ta Trump, masana kasar Sin da Amurka sun tabbatar.
Terry Branstad, jakadan Amurka a China kuma tsohon gwamnan Iowa, babban mai fitar da kayayyakin gona zuwa China, ya ce Beijing na cutar da ma'aikatan Amurka, manoma da kamfanoni.
China, Branstad ya rubuta a cikin wani shafi a jaridar Des Moines Register, yanzu tana ninka zalunci da tallace-tallace na farfaganda a cikin jaridarmu mai zaman kanta.
"A cikin murkushe farfaganda, gwamnatin kasar Sin ta yi amfani da al'adun Amurka na 'yancin magana da' yan jarida ta hanyar sanya tallace-tallace a cikin Des Moines Register", in ji Branstad.
"A akasin wannan, a cikin kantin jarida na kusa da nan a Beijing, za ku iya samun ra'ayoyi kaɗan kuma ba za ku ga ainihin ra'ayoyin da jama'ar kasar Sin za su iya yi game da matsalar tattalin arzikin kasar Sin ba, saboda kafofin watsa labarai suna karkashin ikon jam'iyyar kwaminis ta kasar Sin", in ji shi.
Ya kara da cewa, wata jarida da ta fi kowa karatu a kasar Sin ta ki karbar tayin buga rubutunsa, duk da cewa bai bayyana jaridar da ya gabatar ba.
